				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Wilah!: Waste Sorting Educational Card Game" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Wilah is an educational card with environment theme. Suitable for children, lecturer, environmentalist, or parent who want to teach about how to sort the waste. Wilah can be played by 2-6 player with age 7 and above for 5-15 minutes per game. Wilah involve player's cognitive aspect to sort the waste based on the material and involve player's motoric aspect.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To play, deal the deck out as evenly as possible to every player. Make sure the card remain unrevealed. One by one, each player take the topmost card and stack it to the place that reachable for every player. Under certain condition, player will slap the card and shout &amp;quot;Wilah!&amp;quot;. These conditions are :&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     If three cards show the same color or waste category&amp;#10;     If two cards show the identical image&amp;#10;     If one card show waste processing or trashbin&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player that succeed to slap and shout &amp;quot;Wilah!&amp;quot; can keep all the card with the same category or color as that player slap can. Those card counted as coin. Player with the most coin win the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
